spirit:component.spirit:name: PmodESP32_axi_uartlite_0_0

spirit:field.spirit:name: RST_TXFIFO
spirit:field.spirit:description: Reset/clear the transmit FIFO Writing a 1 to this bit position clears the transmit FIFO 0 - Do nothing 1 - Clear the transmit FIFO

spirit:field.spirit:name: RST_RXFIFO
spirit:field.spirit:description: Reset/clear the receive FIFO Writing a 1 to this bit position clears the receive FIFO 0 - Do nothing 1 - Clear the receive FIFO

spirit:field.spirit:name: Enable_Intr
spirit:field.spirit:description: Enable interrupt for the AXI UART Lite 0 - Disable interrupt signal 1 - Enable interrupt signal

spirit:field.spirit:name: RX_FIFO_Valid_Data
spirit:field.spirit:description: Indicates if the receive FIFO has data. 0 - Receive FIFO is empty 1 - Receive FIFO has data

spirit:field.spirit:name: RX_FIFO_Full
spirit:field.spirit:description: Indicates if the receive FIFO is full. 0 - Receive FIFO is not full 1 - Receive FIFO is full

spirit:field.spirit:name: TX_FIFO_Empty
spirit:field.spirit:description: Indicates if the transmit FIFO is empty. 0 - Transmit FIFO is not empty 1 - Transmit FIFO is empty

spirit:field.spirit:name: TX_FIFO_Full
spirit:field.spirit:description: Indicates if the transmit FIFO is full. 0 - Transmit FIFO is not full 1 - Transmit FIFO is full

spirit:field.spirit:name: Intr_Enabled
spirit:field.spirit:description: Indicates that interrupts is enabled. 0 - Interrupt is disabled 1 - Interrupt is enabled

spirit:field.spirit:name: Overrun_Error
spirit:field.spirit:description: Indicates that a overrun error has occurred after the last time the status register was read. Overrun is when a new character has been received but the receive FIFO is full. The received character is ignored and not written into the receive FIFO. This bit is cleared when the status register is read. 0 - No overrun error has occurred 1 - Overrun error has occurred

spirit:field.spirit:name: Frame_Error
spirit:field.spirit:description: Indicates that a frame error has occurred after the last time the status register was read. Frame error is defined as detection of a stop bit with the value 0. The receive character is ignored and not written to the receive FIFO. This bit is cleared when the status register is read. 0 - No frame error has occurred 1 - Frame error has occurred

spirit:field.spirit:name: Parity_Error
spirit:field.spirit:description: Indicates that a parity error has occurred after the last time the status register was read. If the UART is configured without any parity handling, this bit is always 0. The received character is written into the receive FIFO. This bit is cleared when the status register is read. 0 - No parity error has occurred 1 - Parity error has occurred

spirit:component.spirit:description: Generic UART (Universal Asynchronous Receiver/Transmitter) for AXI Interface

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_DATA_BITS
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: The number of data bits in the serial frame.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_BAUDRATE
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Baud rate of the AXI UART Lite in bits per second.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_S_AXI_ACLK_FREQ_HZ
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: AXI4-Lite clock frequency range should be in between 10 to 300MHz.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: C_S_AXI_ACLK_FREQ_HZ_d
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: AXI4-Lite clock frequency range should be in between 10 to 300MHz.
